{{wiktionary|CRM}}
'''CRM''' may refer to:

{{tocright}}
== Sales and marketing ==
* [[Customer relationship management]], processes implemented to manage a company's interactions with customers and prospects
* [[Cause-related marketing]]
* [[Courtesy reply mail]], a type of business mail

== Companies and institutions ==
* [[Centre de Recherches Mathématiques]], a Canadian mathematical research institute
* [[Centre de Recerca Matemàtica]], a mathematics research institute in Barcelona
* Centre for Regenerative Medicine, at the [[Scottish Centre for Regenerative Medicine]]
* [[Comas Racing Management]], a driver management firm of [[Érik Comas]]
* [[Commander Mexicana]]'s [[Airline codes-C|ICAO code]]

== Management ==
=== Resource management ===
* [[Crew resource management]] or Cockpit Resource Management, an aviation training program
* [[Cultural resources management]]

=== Other management ===
* [[Certified resident manager]], a professional designation in property management
* [[Certified Risk Manager]], a professional designation

== Other uses ==
* [[Cis-regulatory module]], a region of DNA
* [[Caloric restriction mimetic]], a substance that mimics the caloric restriction anti-aging effect
* [[Cardiac rhythm management]]
* [[Certified reference materials]], ‘controls’ or standards used to check the quality and traceability of products
* [[CIDOC Conceptual Reference Model]], an international standard for the exchange of cultural heritage information
* [[Civil rights movement]], a movement for civil and political rights in the United States to abolish public and private acts of racial discrimination between 1954 to 1968
* [[Chittaranjan Mitra]] (1926–2008), or C. R. Mitra, an Indian scientist

== See also ==
* [[CRM 114 (fictional device)]], a device in Stanley Kubrick's film ''Dr. Strangelove''
* [[CRM114 (program)]], a statistical classifier and pattern matching language commonly used to filter spam

